All Classes

Class Description
AbstractContext
Abstract context that is used to group all common methods among all implementations of Context.
AnsiColors
Defines some ANSI colors ready to be used in the project.
ChatOSUtils
Utility class that define constants and methods used in the whole project.
ClientChatOS
Main class for the client.
ClientMessageDisplay
Display class (only used by the client).
Context
Mandatory methods to be an attachement of a SelectionKey.
HTTPLineReader
Reader used to read an HTTP line (i.e. all bytes until HTTPLineReader.CRHTTPLineReader.LF is read).
HTTPPacket
HTTPPacket.type : type (not null) of the packet that can be either: HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType.REQUEST -> in this case every fields are null except HTTPPacket.resource which is the request. HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType.BAD_RESPONSE -> in this case every fields are null except HTTPPacket.resource. HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType.GOOD_RESPONSE -> in this case HTTPPacket.contentType contains the type of the content and HTTPPacket.content contains the content of the HTTP response (the buffer is in read-mode) and HTTPPacket.resource contains the name of the received resource.
HTTPPacket.HTTPPacketType
Type of the HTTPPacket.
HTTPReader
Reader used to read an HTTPPacket that can either be a request or a response.
Packet
Represents a packet circulating between the server and the clients.
Packet.ErrorCode
Possible error codes.
Packet.PacketBuilder
Utility class made to create Packet more easily.
Packet.PacketType
Types of the different packets.
PacketReader
Reader used to read a Packet.
PacketReader.ProcessFailure
Type of failure that can appear.
Reader<T>
A reader is an object that take a buffer (in write-mode) as input and process it to obtain an element of type T.
Reader.ProcessStatus
Current state of the reader.
RejectReader
Reader used to ignore all bytes until the reading ofthe byte RejectReader.ERR_CODE followed by RejectReader.RECOVER_CODE.
ServerChatOS
Main class for the server.
ServerMessageDisplay
Display class (only used by the server).
StringReader
The reader can process a buffer to extract an integer (the length of the message) followed by a string encoded in UTF-8 with the given length.
